    "type": "Requirement",
    "name": "Hemolysis validation verification requirement",
    "description": "The validation activity supporting the RH index acceptance criterion shall be executed as a controlled experiment in which flow rate, rotational speed, and blood priming conditions are independently manipulated and hemolysis outcomes measured under prospectively defined protocol conditions. This ensures that observed RH values can be causally attributed to the pump geometry under test rather than to confounding clinical or patient-specific variables.",
    "requiredVerificationMethod": "controlled-experiment"
  },
