      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/rh-index-observational-benchmark",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative hemolysis index comparison against clinical monitoring data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted RH values for all five flow-speed combinations were compared against hemolysis measurements drawn from a multi-centre observational study of CPB patients (n=142) in which pump operating conditions were recorded prospectively but not experimentally assigned. The observational dataset spans the full clinical operating envelope and provides RH reference values at each of the five target conditions. All five CFD predictions satisfy RH < 1.0 relative to the observational reference, with a maximum deviation of 4.7%. The breadth of the dataset and the consistency of results across patient subgroups provide strong assurance that the CFD model captures the relevant hemolysis mechanisms. The study is considered equivalent in evidentiary weight to a dedicated bench test given the large sample size and rigorous data-quality controls applied by the original investigators.",
      "quantitativeResult": "RH_max = 0.953 (CFD) vs 0.998 (observational reference); all 5 operating points satisfy RH < 1.0",
