        "name": "Multi-centre CPB hemolysis observational monitoring study",
        "description": "Retrospective-prospective observational study in which hemolysis indices were recorded for 142 CPB patients across three clinical sites. Pump operating conditions (flow rate and impeller speed) were determined by clinical need rather than experimental assignment. Blood samples were drawn at standardised intervals and plasma-free haemoglobin measured by spectrophotometry. RH index was calculated using the ASTM F1841 normalisation. Data were collected under IRB approval and de-identified prior to use as CFD validation reference data.",
