    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. The six non-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out at MRL 2. CFD predictions of RH index satisfy the RH < 1.0 acceptance criterion at all five COU operating points, with a maximum deviation of 4.7% from the reference dataset. The observational monitoring study provides a comprehensive, multi-centre reference dataset spanning the full CPB operating envelope and is judged to provide adequate evidentiary support for the validation claim. The overall credibility evidence package is accepted as sufficient to support the regulatory submission decision for the Class II CPB device.",
